    public class DefaultFlow<ST extends DefaultFlowState>
extends AbstractFlow<ST>
    The default implementation of the flow-sensitive type inference.

      • propagateFromType

        protected void propagateFromType(Tree lhs,
                     AnnotatedTypeMirror rhs)
        Description copied from class: AbstractFlow
        Moves bits in an assignment using a type instead of a tree.

        #propagate(Tree, Tree) is preferred, since it is able to use extra information about the right-hand side (such as its element). This method should only be used when a type (and nothing else) is available, such as when checking the variable in an enhanced for loop against the iterated type (which is the type argument of an Iterable).

        Specified by:
        propagateFromType in class AbstractFlow<ST extends DefaultFlowState>
        Parameters:
        lhs - the left-hand side of the assignment
        rhs - the type of the right-hand side of the assignment
